# Skills opt-in (project)

Files under `.cursor/skills/` (including `SKILL.md` and any nested resources) are **manual-only** for this workspace.

**Do not** read, summarize, or follow any skill unless the user:

1. **@mentions** that skill in chat (Cursor skill mention or `@` path to the skill folder / `SKILL.md`), or  
2. **Explicitly asks** to use a named skill (e.g. “use the architecture skill”, “follow lint-and-validate”).

This applies to **every** skill in `.cursor/skills/`, including any added in the future.

If you need an overview of paths, ask the user to @mention the **`esoterica-skills`** rule (catalog) or to name the skill they want.
